===Intransitive Verb===
'''ad-lib, ad-libbing, ad-libbed'''
# to [[improvise]] in speaking, often in relation to comedy.
===Quotations===
*'''1998''': Hope’s onstage '''ad-libbing''' generated more humor and attention than the show’s lacklustre libretto. &mdash; ''The New Yorker,'' 21 Dec 1998
*'''2004''': I watched Jeb Bush as his brother spoke. He paid attention, grinned and laughed, even '''ad-libbed''' when called upon. &mdash; ''The New Yorker,'' 15 Mar 2004

